abstract: "DTQEM v20.0 simulates the decay of bipartite entanglement in a two‑qubit system under continuous local dephasing and thermal relaxation. Starting from the Bell state |Φ⁺⟩, we apply a fixed Hamiltonian and pure dephasing L = √(γ_φ0 E_ext)(σ_z⊗I) on Alice, together with thermal baths on both qubits (rates derived from T₁ and temperature). Using experimental parameters for a superconducting transmon (T₁=T₂=1.68 ms), we compute concurrence C(t) and CHSH S(t) as functions of time. The entanglement lifetime τ_ent decreases with stronger measurement (Zeno effect) and drops dramatically at T=1 K, consistent with measured coherence times. The code is open‑source, numerically validated, and includes a database of five qubit types (trapped ion, transmon, processor‑grade transmon, silicon spin, quantum dot)."
